Cell.Data: Prime Minister Tomiichi Murayama on the 28th held a press conference with Cabinet reporters for the new year at his official residence and said of the New Democratic League members' move to break away from the Socialist Party of Japan, "It will not affect the administration. Even if there are some who will actually leave the party, I think the move would not extend any further," indicating that this issue would not result in the formation of a mass breakaway group.
